            <Property name="rows" type="int" value="5"/>
            <Property name="text" type="java.lang.String" value="This system is a modern attendance management solution powered by AI-based face recognition. It eliminates the need for manual or ID-based&#xa; attendance by using facial features to identify and mark attendance securely and automatically.&#xa;&#xa;Key Features:&#xa;                     Real-time Face Recognition using state-of-the-art InsightFace (ArcFace + RetinaFace)&#xa;                     Secure &amp; Reliable: Only registered faces are recognized&#xa;                     Automatic Cooldown: Prevents multiple entries within 5 seconds&#xa;                     Student &amp; Teacher Mode for role-based access&#xa;                     MySQL Database Integration for storing attendance logs&#xa;                     Java Swing or Flask UI for user interaction&#xa;                     Webcam-based live image processing&#xa;&#xa;Technology Stack:&#xa;                      Backend: Python &#xa;                      Face Recognition: InsightFace (buffalo_s, ArcFace, RetinaFace)&#xa;                      Frontend: Java Swing&#xa;                      Database: MySQL&#xa;                      Others: OpenCV, Tkinter, threading/multiprocessing&#xa;How It Works:&#xa;                       Registration: The user provides a face image or captures it via webcam.&#xa;                       Detection: When the system is running, it continuously scans faces using the webcam.&#xa;                       Verification: Matches the detected face with the registered dataset using InsightFace.&#xa;                       UI Panel: User interface shows dashboard, user registration, view logs, etc.&#xa;Motivation:&#xa;                 Traditional attendance methods (manual, RFID, card swipes) are time-consuming, prone to fraud, or require expensive hardware. This&#xa;                 project provides an efficient, low-cost, and AI-driven alternative tailored for schools, colleges, and offices.&#xa;Developed By:   Manu Kumar &#xa;Guided By :        Rakesh Kumar Godi Sir"/>
          </Properties>
        </Component>
      </SubComponents>
    </Container>
